  "dataNotes": [
    "v3.2 minimal Waterloo data slice for JSON/schema integration.",
    "Uses napoleonic_unit_templates.json through ScenarioCatalog.unitTemplateName.",
    "Napoleonic templates use v3.3 ComponentType cases; morale now has a minimal Division-level model, while formation, cavalry charge, and artillery preparation rules remain future work.",
    "v3.5 adds delayed French and Prussian reinforcement schedule entries; runtime deployment waits for safe controlled entry hexes.",
    "v3 data follow-up adds Plancenoit as a French-held objective and adds minimal La Haye Sainte / Papelotte garrisons without changing the current Waterloo victory conditions.",
    "v3 data follow-up adds q5,r1 Wavre Road as an abstract Prussian rear road, supply, and reinforcement entry hex; Prussian Arrival Road at q4,r1 remains the objective trigger and victory-condition member.",
    "v3 data follow-up adds an Anglo-Allied left reserve at Papelotte to make the coalition left wing less skeletal without changing objective or victory-condition data.",
    "v3 data follow-up adds a Prussian Approach screen at q4,r0 to make Blucher's arrival axis visible without changing objective, victory-condition, or reinforcement trigger data.",
    "v3 data follow-up aligns French Cavalry Reserve reinforcement hp with the cavalry_reserve template maxHP without changing reinforcement timing or trigger data.",
    "Not the final 80-160 hex Waterloo campaign map."
  ]
